  "market_context": "NQ trading within a daily range. Price had established a high and a low, then formed a failure swing, before sweeping the range low and closing back inside, while leaving untouched failure swings on the highs.",
  "key_observation": "When high resistance liquidity forms on the lows (a swept low) and failure swings rest on the highs, this combination supports a long bias targeting the unswept failure swing highs above.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identify the daily range structure on NQ, noting an established high, low, and a failure swing within the range.",
    "Observe that price sweeps the range low and closes back inside, converting that low into high resistance liquidity.",
    "Check the highs and confirm that failure swings (unswept highs) remain above, representing draw on liquidity.",
    "Combine the two observations: high resistance liquidity on the lows plus failure swings on the highs adds to a long bias.",
    "Play it forward and confirm that price runs the failure swing high above, validating the bias."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price ran the failure swing high above, confirming the long bias setup.",
  "lessons": "On the daily chart, mapping where high resistance liquidity sits versus where failure swings remain unswept is a simple bias-building exercise—price tends to protect high resistance liquidity and reach toward failure swings.",
